## Elementals
Elementals are ageless, ever-changing spirits of the primal forces that forge worlds; volatile beings of raw elemental power, manifested in physical form. The most common primordial form of life has been these elementals, who come before any organic life is ever able to be born, and will persist long after all organic life has perished.

***Base Primal Forces.*** The elements are a complex hotbed of different forces and interactions, but for the most part, four primary materials are manifested. These are, of course, fire, water, earth and air; the building blocks of the world. 

***Spiritual Conflict.*** The fifth element is said to be spirit, the inner energy of all living beings. Worlds with strong spirit are tranquil and manifest few elemental spirits who act in harmony. However, worlds with compromised spirit will result in all-out war that can shatter and recreate the surface of the world multiple times in a day.

Azeroth was one such world, where its four Elemental Lords fought for countless millenia. Mountains, volcanoes, oceans and storms rose and fell rapidly as one lord gained ground over another.

***Bound to the Elemental Plane.*** On Azeroth, as the titanic Keepers saw to the ordering of the world, they found the elementals wreaking havoc under the corrupting influence of the Old Gods. As a safeguard, the Keepers constructed the Elemental Plane as a prison in which the elemental lords could be locked away. In their absence, the Keepers could tend to their task at hand; settling the natural order of Azeroth.

The Elemental Plane is intimately connected to the world of Azeroth, preventing all but the weakest manifestations of elemental power in the world. It is divided into four interlinked realms: the Abyssal Maw, realm of water; Deepholm, realm of earth; the Firelands, realm of fire; and Skywall, realm of air.

***Shamanic Allies.*** Much of the responsibilities of the elements to maintain the balance of the world falls into the hands of the shamans. Shamans commune with them using spiritual magic, borrowing their powers only at the elements' permission. Because of this, shamans are forever devoted to a cycle of favor and thanks, gaining great power in exchange for reverence, loyalty, or whatever other small favors the spirits may seek.

***Elemental Instability.*** Even the Titanic prison cannot fully keep the forces of the world locked away, and any place of major elemental significance is likely to have a few minor elementals roaming around. Ancient springs, deep canyons, and especially volcanoes and powerful storms all may spawn elementals. 

Similarly, skilled spellcasters can summon more powerful elementals directly from their home plane. An elemental spawned this way will be bound in a pair of bracers, necessarily limiting their power and binding them to the command of whoever summoned them.

***Elemental Nature.*** Elementals do not eat, drink or sleep. They do not feel pain, and if they are killed, they will return to their home plane. They will die permanently only if killed while in their home plane.

\columnbreak

