\pagebreakNum

### Air Elementals
Taking the form of a swirling vortex of air, a collection of clouds and static, or even an almost humanoid amalgam of storm, frost, or dust, the elementals of air command the realm of the sky. Turbulent gales and gentle breezes tell locals the mood of the element of air, while fierce lightning lashes at whomever may have angered them.

***Thunderbolts and Lightning.*** The wrath of storms is among the most catastrophic and impressive shows of pure power within nature. Shamans wielding lightning grasp extraordinary amounts of energy, perhaps more than any other force at their call, and these shamans are careful to wield it with caution.

***The Four Winds.*** The world's winds are categorized among the four cardinal directions: North, East, South, and West. Each wind carries with it a different aspect of the weather. 

The frigid North Wind carries blizzards, sleet storms and cold snaps; while the swelling East Wind brings with it storm force winds, gales, cyclones and hurricanes. The South Wind carries brutal thunderstorms from the sea, crashing lightning, rain, and clinging static; while  with the West Wind comes gentle breezes, carrying the changing of winter to spring, scented with pollen.

#### Skywall
The realm of air, Skywall, takes the form of astonishing white and gold palaces that stretch into a clear sunny sky, seemingly crafted out of the clouds themselves. Ever buffeted by gentle breezes, the towering jeweled archi- tecture possesses few floors or stairways; the chief mode of travel in the realm of air is free flight, a feature every denizen possesses. 

***Elemental Hierarchy.*** Sitting atop the the Throne of the Four Winds is Al'Akir the Windlord. Below him are his four lieutenants - the Conclave of Wind - who act as secondary rulers of each of the four winds. Leadership of the four winds is in flux, changing anytime their political foes decide that their time as lords is over. Al'akir, of course, watches the struggles for power with amusement, firm in the knowledge that his own rule is undisputed.

***Cunning Winds.*** More than the swirling power of the sky, the element of air is most associated with intellect and cunning. Its elemental masters rule the skies with royal authority, manipulating the complex systems of friend and foe within their own realm in much the same way as a mortal government. 

***Subjects of Skywall.*** These elemental creatures range widely, from spectres of the faintest squalls to mighty stormclouds given humanoid shape. Fierce elementals in the shape of Azeroth's dragons, known as storm dragons, guard Skywall's paths and bridges, while the spirits of howling gales threaten to blow smaller entities away. In the finest temples stand the djinn, swirling sultans of the winds, acting out the Windlord’s highest commands.


