<div class='footnote'>ELEMENTALS </div>

\pagebreakNum

### Arcane Elementals
Some entities much like elementals form out of other primordial forces. In the case of places overflowing with arcane power, the energy will manifest arcane elementals, similarly bound by bracers and similarly populated by inscrutable minds that seem to act on the seemingly random nature of the arcane itself.

***A Mage's Best Servant.*** As accumulations of arcane energy, arcane elementals can be crafted and bound into service by powerful mages. It is not uncommon to find numerous lesser elementals being used as simple servants in magical academies and cities such as Silvermoon or Dalaran.

***Arcane Anomalies.*** Arcane elementals are rare anomalies, and are most commonly seen in places suffused with arcane power. This makes them relatively common at the sites of exposed ley lines, the magical channels that flow under the surface of planets like blood vessels. 

***Ley Lines.*** Ley lines are channels of immense arcane power that runs all along the surface of a planet in an interconnected web. They are usually buried deep in the earth, visible only to the eyes of those deeply attuned to magic such as the blue dragonflight. Those that are exposed to the surface usually begin to crystallize in the form of glowing purple mana crystals. They have been used for many things, such as creation of moonwells to powering portal spells. 

Ley lines form and change based on the locations of their nexuses--areas where multiple ley lines cross or spring forth from, usually in areas of magical significance and intense use of magic such as cities with large mage academies, blue dragon nesting grounds, or ancient Titan installations.

> ##### Variant: Arcane Elemental Familiar
> Lesser arcane elementals can sometimes be found in the service of powerful mages, acting as servants and carrying out menial tasks. 
>
> ***Familiar.*** The elemental can be bound into serving another creature as a familiar, forming a telepathic bond with its willing master. While the two are bonded, the master can sense what the elemental senses as long as they are within 1 mile of each other. While the elemental is within 10 feet if its master, the master shares the elemental's Magic Resistance trait. If its master causes it physical harm, the elemental will end its service as a familiar, breaking the telepathic bond.

\columnbreak

