> - **Damage Resistances** bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from nonmagical attacks
> - **Damage Immunities** fire, poison
> - **Condition Immunities** exhaustion, grappled, paralyzed, petrified, poisoned, prone, restrained, unconscious
> - **Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 10
> - **Languages** understands Eredun but does not speak
> - **Challenge** 8 (3,900 XP)
> ___
> ***Reckless.*** At the start of its turn, the elemental can gain advantage on all melee weapon attack rolls during that turn, but attack rolls against it have advantage until the start of its next turn.
>
> ***Fel Flames.*** Fire damage that the elemental deals ignores other creatures' fire resistance and immunity.
> 
> ***Heat Aura.*** A creature that hits the elemental with a melee attack while within 10 feet of the elemental or ends their turn there takes 3 (1d6) fire damage.
> 
> ***Illumination.*** The elemental sheds bright light in a 60-foot radius and dim light in an additional 60 feet. 
> 
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The elemental makes two claw attacks.
>
> ***Claw.*** *Melee Weapon Attack.* +8 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. Hit: 11 (2d6 + 5) fire damage.
>
> ***Fel Fireball (Recharge 5-6).*** The elemental creates a blast of green flame at a point it can see within 60 feet of it. Each creature within 20 feet of that point must make a DC 16 Dexterity saving throw, taking 17 (5d6) fire damage on a failed save, or half as much on a success. The elemental is immune to its own attack.
> <br>    Creatures who fail their save have their protections against flame stripped away, gaining vulnerability to fire damage until the beginning of the elemental's next turn.

