\pagebreakNum

### Fire Elementals
<!-- A fire elemental manifests as a smoldering pillar of unwavering destruction. While susceptible to water, it is a cunning presence that will often attempt to overwhelm and outright engulf those who try to stand in its way. -->

A cruel-eyed face staring out of a body like the smoldering of a furnace freed of its constraints. Overwhelming heat crisps the ground around it, and shimmers the air, even as a fire elemental reaches out, eager to spread the flames of its never-ending rage.

***Burning Passion.*** Fire is, in a word, the element of passion. This is a two-sided coin, as spirits of fire are as vulnerable to extreme fits of blinding rage as they are to good humour, though the former is far more common. They are creatures of immediate need, representing both the burning heat that forged the world and the joy and anger of consciousness.

***Fiery Gifts.*** More than any other element, the realm of fire has involved itself in the affairs of mortals. This ranges from simple matters such as fire elementals taking part in Summer festivals, to things as complex as whole mountain ranges being ruled by powerful fire lords, or mutations of mortal races into fire elementals. 

#### The Firelands
A simple name to elucidate the core of a place; the plane of fire is an endless sky of burning, blazing smog, filled with small islands of volcanic rock. The intense heat is enough to set ablaze anything not of the realm, and water is a thing of fantasy. Rivers of molten lava split the dry rock, while irregular igneous rock grows and cools into grand shapes, ever changing the landscape.

***Elemental Hierarchy.*** Ruling from the Sulfuron Keep is Ragnaros the Firelord, with the second in command being his Majordomo. Below them are the various Lords and Barons of the Firelands. A lord's rank is determined by his martial prowess, as to gain and hold your position you must be capable of defeating all who would contest your power.

***Lords of Cinder.*** The Firelands are a militant place, kept under a strict hierarchy of command with ascension in rank coming exclusively through rite of succession; the fiery lieutenants of the Firelord have for eons remained in charge by holding off competitors at every turn. There is no subtlety in the Firelands, and combat is determined quickly, and to the bitter end, inevitably resulting in a group of lords that is both ancient, and unrelenting.

***Ruler of Blackrock.*** Long ago, Ragnaros was summoned by the Dark Iron dwarves as part of their war against their Bronzebeard and Wildhammer kinsmen. His arrival shattered the Redridge Mountains, created the Burning Steppes and Searing Gorge, and turned Blackrock Mountain into an active volcano. The surviving Dark Iron dwarves were enslaved by the Firelord and his lieutenants, acting as his tools for hundreds of years while he gathered his strength in the Molten Core, awaiting the time he could burn all of Azeroth to ash.

***Forces of the Firelands.*** Empty fields of cracked ground are patrolled by its denizens, including by far the largest amount of fleshy creatures of any elemental plane; molten magma giants, two-headed core hounds, serpentine flamewakers and their skeletal hound pets. Huge worms swim and hunt in the magma rivers, while beautiful giant fire hawks blaze across the sky.

\columnbreak

