### Ice Elementals
Manifest from frozen water, ice elementals share domain and allegiance with other water elementals. It moves unhindered through the icy reaches in which it dwells, and is very quick to enrage at the sight of fire wielded in its vicinity.

***Unclear Origins.*** Ice elementals are one of the anomalous mysteries of the elemental world. Some shamans say they are simply a rare type of water elemental, frozen in form and associated with water in its solid state. Others claim that some ice elementals are unnatural conglomerate elementals of ice and earth, formed in unknown circumstances, who represent and govern the changing of summer to winter. The truth is unknown, as the only ones with that knowledge - the elementals themselves - are notorious for keeping their secrets close.

***Scattered Peoples.*** Unlike other elementals, there are no real homes for these creatures of ice. They tend to be found on their own or in small groups located around mountaintop glaciers or large ice floes. Only in Northrend are there large numbers of ice elementals, due to the eternal winter that grips most of the continent.

***The Ice Stone has Melted.*** The master elemental of frost is undoubtedly Ahune, the Frost Lord, a poorly-tempered elemental of immense power. Ahune, easily manipulated, seeks yearly to bring an end to the hated heat of high Summer, and at this time frost elementals will manifest across the globe, seeking to cool it through the creation of vast obelisks of ice. It is a plan doomed to fail, <br/> of course, and Ahune’s persistence is held at bay on each summer solstice through shamanic ritual. 

