<div class="pageLetter">E</div>
<div class='footnote'>ELEMENTALS </div>

\pagebreakNum

## Elemental Revenants

The elemental revenants are yet another long-unsolved mystery among many others out in the frozen land of Northrend. Far up at the cap of the world, these elemental spirits appear to be bound within enormous, ancient sets of rough-hewn armor, drifting along above the ground as though caught in gentle breeze. They are rare and, when seen, often appear to be following some kind of distant, obscure desire to stand guard, following no apparent patterns or goals beyond protecting a single area for centuries at a time.

***Mysterious Origins.*** Though they are elemental in nature, these entities are vanishingly rare outside of Northrend, and are not seen in their respective elemental planes. It is yet unknown why they act and appear the way they do, or even if they originated as elementals.

***Complex Loyalties.*** Some of the revenants of Northrend have been seen serving a mysterious master in the mountains, though for what purpose, to what end, and how deep this loyalty lies is unknown.

***Tundra Ghosts.*** The revenants that drift across the snow, barely visible through blizzards and mist, have a ghostly, ethereal quality to them, and are believed by some local cultures to be the spirits of dead warriors bound eternally to their armor. 

### Air Revenant
Arcing electricity and static clinging to armour or weapons herald the arrival of an air or lightning revenant, twisted ribbons of rough metal wrapped around a powerful vortex. Lightning comes to their aid, wielded like a club, while the currents of air around them whip and tug at their foes. Their voices, shrill shrieks, are that of the most violent of icy gales.

### Death Revenant
A mystery even greater than the cause of elemental revenants is the death revenants, so seldom seen as to border on mythical. Spoken of in hushed tones, and only when the sun is high, these fell spirits are said to be spirits of death itself. Great black scythes are wielded empty metal husks, who move eerily silent and speak only to the mind. It is unknown if these dread reapers are even of the same ilk as other revenants, and their desires are, once again, a mystery.

### Earth Revenant
Plumes of stones and dry earth support stout, sturdy plates roughly riveted together. A massive club, thick enough to topple walls, drifts nearby. An earth revenant wields pure, raw power, roaming their territories slowly, with the assurance that any opposition will be completely flattened. 

### Fire Revenant
Jagged, scaled armor kept red-hot by the blazing flames within, a fire revenant resembles a floating foundry, spewing molten slag and burning coals in its wake. Unlike most revenants, their weapons are well-crafted and often beautiful, albeit hot enough to brand their foes with artful scars. When rarely seen outdoors in Northrend, the extreme heat flowing out of their bodies clashes with the cold and blankets them in steam.

\columnbreak

### Water Revenant
Smooth pots or jugs - connected to a water revenant's armoured body by thick chains - constantly spill out with the clear, freezing water that comprises the vague appearance of a body. Frigid temperatures accompany these revenants, who may well be the most at home in the icy land of Northrend. Water ebbs and flows at their command, frostbite awaits anyone at the receiving end of their jagged, cruel scimitars. 

